ague players]]\n[[Category:FC DAC 1904 Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda players]]\n[[Category:Xanthi F.C. players]]\n[[Category:AC Sparta Prague players]]\n[[Category:Selangor FA players]]\n[[Category:FK \u010c\u00e1slav players]]\n[[Category:Cameroonian expatriate sportspeople in Slovakia]]\n[[Category:Cameroonian expatriate sportspeople in Greece]]\n[[Category:Cameroonian expatriate sportspeople in the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Cameroonian expatriate sportspeople in France]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Slovakia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Greece]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Iran]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in France]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in the Czech Republic]]\n\n\n{{Cameroon-footy-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Martin Abena\n| image = Martin Abena.jpg\n| caption = Abena in October 2011\n| fullname = Martin Achille Biholong Abena\n| height = 1.90 m\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1986|6|14|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Yaound\u00e9]], Cameroon\n| currentclub = \n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1 = \n| youthclubs1 = \n| years1 = 2004\u20132005\n| clubs1 = [[Raon-l'Etape]]\n| caps1 = \n| goals1 = \n| years2 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs2 = [[Pegah F.C.|Pegah Gilan]]\n| caps2 = 11 \n| goals2 = 0\n| years3 = 2008\n| clubs3 = [[FK DAC 1904 Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda|Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda]]\n| caps3 = 30\n| goals3 = 2\n| years4 = 2009\n| clubs4 = [[Skoda Xanthi]]\n| caps4 = 23\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2010\u20132011\n| clubs5 = [[FK DAC 1904 Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda|Dunajsk\u00e1 Streda]]\n| caps5 = 10\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs6 = [[AC Sparta Prague|Sparta Prague]]\n| caps6 = 7\n| goals6 = 0\n| years7 = 2012\u20132013\n| clubs7 = [[PFC Lokomotiv Sofia]]\n| caps7 = 25\n| goals7 = 6\n| years8 = 2013\u20132014\n| clubs8 = [[Selangor FA|Selangor]]\n| caps8 = \n| goals8 = \n| years9 = 2014\u20132015\n| clubs9 = [[FK \u01