{"title_page": "Johnny Weeks", "text_new": "{{Infobox character\n| color              = #1F1F1F\n| name               = Johnny Weeks\n| series             = [[The Wire]]\n| image              = [[Image:The Wire Johnny.jpg|right|250px|Johnny Weeks, an unfortunate drug addict played by Leo Fitzpatrick]]\n| first              = \"[[The Target (The Wire)|The Target]]\" (2002)\n| last               = \"[[Mission Accomplished (The Wire)|Mission Accomplished]]\" (2004)\n| creator            = [[David Simon (writer)|David Simon]]\n| portrayer          = [[Leo Fitzpatrick]]\n| occupation         = Drug addict, scrap stealer\n| gender             = Male\n}}\n'''Johnny Weeks''' is a fictional character on the [[HBO]] drama series ''[[The Wire (TV series)|The Wire]]'', portrayed by [[Leo Fitzpatrick]]. A [[opioid use disorder|heroin addict]], he commits a series of petty crimes to afford his habit, along with fellow addict [[Bubbles (The Wire)|Bubbles]].\n\n==Biography==\n\n===Season 1===\nIn season 1, Johnny is Bubbles' best friend and a drug addict with notoriously bad luck. He is naive and enthusiastic for \"the game\", and allows Bubbles to play the role of teacher. In the pilot episode Johnny is badly beaten by [[Bodie Broadus]], [[Poot Carr]], and other dealers after trying to pass counterfeit money to [[D'Angelo Barksdale]]'s operation. This spurs Bubbles to become a police informant, but Johnny disapproves and takes no part in it except when arrested by the police.\n\nWhile in the hospital for that beating, Johnny discovers he is [[HIV positive]]; he also undergoes a [[colostomy]] operation.\n\n===Season 2===\nJohnny is first seen by Detective [[Jimmy McNulty]], stealing from a shopping centre with Bubbles. McNulty catches Johnny and Bubbles, but instead of arresting them asks them to find stick up artist [[Omar Little]]. At the end of Season 2, [[Police of The Wire#Michael Santangelo|Officer Santangelo]] arrests Bubbles and Johnny stealing [[morphine]] from an ambulance. They are released because Bubbles gives information about [[Proposition Joe]]'s dealers at the projects, when [[Cheese Wagstaff|Cheese]] is shot in the shoulder by [[Brother Mouzone]].\n\n===Season 3===\nJohnny and Bubbles continue to steal from scrapyards. Bubbles would rather make money by continuing to inform detectives [[Jimmy McNulty|McNulty]] and [[Kima Greggs|Greggs]]. Johnny overdoses, and his body is discovered in a vacant house in [[Howard \"Bunny\" Colvin|Major Colvin]]'s \"Hamsterdam\" free zone.\n\n==Origins==\nJohnny is based on a young white homeless addict [[David Simon]] met while researching ''[[The Corner]]''.{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{unreferenced|date=May 2013}}\n\n{{The Wire}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Weeks, Johnny}}\n[[Category:The Wire characters]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2002]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters based on real people]]\n[[Category:Fictional career criminals]]\n[[Category:Fictional heroin users]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with HIV/AIDS]]\n[[Category:Fictional homeless people]]\n[[Category:Male characters in television]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox character\n| color              = #1F1F1F\n| name               = Johnny Weeks\n| series             = [[The Wire]]\n| image              = [[Image:The Wire Johnny.jpg|right|250px|Johnny Weeks, an unfortunate drug addict played by Leo Fitzpatrick]]\n| first              = \"[[The Target (The Wire)|The Target]]\" (2002)\n| last               = \"[[Mission Accomplished (The Wire)|Mission Accomplished]]\" (2004)\n| creator            = [[David Simon (writer)|David Simon]]\n| portrayer          = [[Leo Fitzpatrick]]\n| occupation         = Drug addict, scrap stealer\n| gender             = Male\n}}\n'''Johnny Weeks''' is a fictional character on the [[HBO]] drama series ''[[The Wire (TV series)|The Wire]]'', portrayed by [[Leo Fitzpatrick]]. A [[opioid use disorder|heroin addict]], he commits a series of petty crimes to afford his habit, along with fellow addict [[Bubbles (The Wire)|Bubbles]].\n\n==Biography==\n\n===Season 1===\nIn season 1, Johnny is Bubbles' best friend and a drug addict with notoriously bad luck. He is naive and enthusiastic for \"the game\", and allows Bubbles to play the role of teacher. In the pilot episode Johnny is badly beaten by [[Bodie Broadus]], [[Poot Carr]], and other dealers after trying to pass counterfeit money to [[D'Angelo Barksdale]]'s operation. This spurs Bubbles to become a police informant, but Johnny disapproves and takes no part in it except when arrested by the police.\n\nWhile in the hospital for that beating, Johnny discovers he is [[HIV positive]]; he also undergoes a [[colostomy]] operation.\n\n===Season 2===\nJohnny is first seen by Detective [[Jimmy McNulty]], stealing from a shopping centre with Bubbles. McNulty catches Johnny and Bubbles, but instead of arresting them asks them to find stick up artist [[Omar Little]]. At the end of Season 2, [[Police of The Wire#Michael Santangelo|Officer Santangelo]] arrests Bubbles and Johnny stealing [[morphine]] from an ambulance. They are released because Bubbles gives information about [[Proposition Joe]]'s dealers at the projects, when [[Cheese Wagstaff|Cheese]] is shot in the shoulder by [[Brother Mouzone]].\n\n===Season 3===\nJohnny and Bubbles continue to steal from scrapyards. Bubbles would rather make money by continuing to inform detectives [[Jimmy McNulty|McNulty]] and [[Kima Greggs|Greggs]]. Johnny overdoses, and his body is discovered in a vacant house in [[Howard \"Bunny\" Colvin|Major Colvin]]'s \"Hamsterdam\" free zone.\n\n==Origins==\nJohnny is based on a young white homeless addict [[David Simon]] met while researching ''[[The Corner]]''.{{citation needed|date=April 2019}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{unreferenced|date=May 2013}}\n\n{{The Wire}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Weeks, Johnny}}\n[[Category:The Wire characters]]\n[[Category:Television characters introduced in 2002]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters based on real people]]\n[[Category:Fictional career criminals]]\n[[Category:Fictional heroin users]]\n[[Category:Fictional American people of Danish descent]]\n[[Category:Fictional characters with HIV/AIDS]]\n[[Category:Fictional homeless people]]\n[[Category:Male characters in television]]\n", "name_user": "TheImaCow", "label": "safe", "comment": "removedCategory:Fictional American people of Danish descentusingHotCat", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Johnny_Weeks"}
